                     /synonym="HK022 attachment site (phage)"
                     /note="HK022 phage attachment (att) site: the Int (tyrosine
                     recombinase) recombination substrate that carries the
                     arm-type and core-type Int-binding sites flanking the
                     crossover overlap (O) region. Source-verified against
                     X51962 (complement strand 229..486, 100% identity over 258
                     bp). The 27 bp O-region (overlap/core) lies at positions
                     203..230 on the plus strand and is conserved with the
                     lambda att core. NOTE: although the catalog slug is 'attB',
                     this exact sequence is the phage attP region of X51962
                     (annotated [242:469] on the plus strand of the deposit);
                     the bacterial attB proper lies in the E. coli leuX tRNA-Leu
                     gene. See recommendations."
